  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 2.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The seed of Israel separated themselves from all strangers.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Compare ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 10:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", by which it appears that the \"strangers\" are \"the people of the lands,\" or neighbouring heathen, of whom there were at all times considerable numbers in Jerusalem (comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 13:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). It was not fitting that these aliens should take part in a ceremony of which the main object was that the special people of God should renew their covenant with him. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Stood and confessed.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Attitude is perhaps scarcely intended here, since the Jews confessed their sins kneeling (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 9:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), or prostrate (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 10:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Hence we hear in the next verse that they \"stood up,\" or \"rose up\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "consurrexerunt",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", Vulg.). Nehemiah 9:2",
